01:45:29,851 --> 01:45:30,851
Becky moved to sit down as Natalie read from
the newspaper.

1951
01:45:30,851 --> 01:45:31,851
'"It is clear from the diary that Leslie Newman
knew the Keegan family," said Detective Troy

1952
01:45:31,851 --> 01:45:32,851
Jameson late yesterday afternoon.

1953
01:45:32,851 --> 01:45:33,851
"However, Newman denies having killed the
girl."

1954
01:45:33,851 --> 01:45:34,851
In the diary, Newman also describes his feelings
of hopelessness after being accused and says

1955
01:45:34,851 --> 01:45:35,851
that he feels unable to stand up to a family
of wealth and influence like the Scanlon's.

1956
01:45:35,851 --> 01:45:36,851
He is deeply upset by the effect of the scandal
on his family.

1957
01:45:36,851 --> 01:45:37,851
He writes that at the time Charles Scanlon
said he had seen him with Lizzie Keegan, Newman

1958
01:45:37,851 --> 01:45:38,851
had, in fact, been playing on the beach with
his son.

1959
01:45:38,851 --> 01:45:39,851
He remembers seeing a Keegan girl in the distance
but it wasn't Lizzie.

1960
01:45:39,851 --> 01:45:40,851
It was her younger sister, Ruth Keegan.'

1961
01:45:40,851 --> 01:45:41,851
Natalie put the paper down.

1962
01:45:41,851 --> 01:45:42,851
'He saw Ruth?' said Becky, puzzled.

1963
01:45:42,851 --> 01:45:43,851
'Did she mention that she saw him?' asked
Natalie.

1964
01:45:43,851 --> 01:45:44,851
'No,' said Becky.

1965
01:45:44,851 --> 01:45:45,851
She looked at the newspaper.

1966
01:45:45,851 --> 01:45:46,851
'I'd better go and see her.

1967
01:45:46,851 --> 01:45:47,851
She'll be upset if she's seen this.'

1968
01:45:47,851 --> 01:45:48,851
Becky read a bit more of the newspaper story
and then went over the road to see Ruth.

1969
01:45:48,851 --> 01:45:49,851
She was down on the beach, Shirl told her,
not far from the cottages.

1970
01:45:49,851 --> 01:45:50,851
Becky went to find her.

1971
01:45:50,851 --> 01:45:51,851
'The police wanted to see me yesterday,' said
Ruth as Becky sat down next to her on the

1972
01:45:51,851 --> 01:45:52,851
sand.

1973
01:45:52,851 --> 01:45:53,851
'Have you read the newspaper?'

1974
01:45:53,851 --> 01:45:54,851
'Yes,' said Becky.

1975
01:45:54,851 --> 01:45:55,851
'Radcliff was his mother's maiden name,' said
Ruth, looking out at the sea.

1976
01:45:55,851 --> 01:45:56,851
Becky nodded.

1977
01:45:56,851 --> 01:45:57,851
'I suppose she changed her name because of
the scandal.

1978
01:45:57,851 --> 01:45:58,851
And the horror of it all.'

1979
01:45:58,851 --> 01:45:59,851
Becky looked at her.

1980
01:45:59,851 --> 01:46:00,851
'Are you all right, Ruth?'

1981
01:46:00,851 --> 01:46:01,851
Ruth didn't answer the question.

1982
01:46:01,851 --> 01:46:02,851
'She never really recovered,' she said, 'and
she never told John Radcliff about his father's

1983
01:46:02,851 --> 01:46:03,851
diary.

1984
01:46:03,851 --> 01:46:04,851
He only found it about a month ago, when his
mother died.

1985
01:46:04,851 --> 01:46:05,851
Apparently, before that he didn't know it
existed.

1986
01:46:05,851 --> 01:46:06,851
The police got the story from a neighbour.'

1987
01:46:06,851 --> 01:46:07,851
Ruth let out a long breath.

1988
01:46:07,851 --> 01:46:08,851
'After Radcliff read the diary he couldn't
stop talking about what he thought he'd discovered.

1989
01:46:08,851 --> 01:46:09,851
He told anyone who'd listen that he was going
to talk to Scanlon and find out the truth.

1990
01:46:09,851 --> 01:46:10,851
Apparently, no one really believed him.

1991
01:46:10,851 --> 01:46:11,851
They thought he was just an ex-criminal talking
big.'

1992
01:46:11,851 --> 01:46:12,851
A man and a boy ran into the water in front
of them.

1993
01:46:12,851 --> 01:46:13,851
'But he did go to see Scanlon,' said Becky.

1994
01:46:13,851 --> 01:46:14,851
'At his house.'

1995
01:46:14,851 --> 01:46:15,851
'Yes,' replied Ruth.

1996
01:46:15,851 --> 01:46:16,851
They watched the man and the boy playing.'

1997
01:46:16,851 --> 01:46:17,851
'The police think John Radcliff came to Rottnest
to find me,' she said quietly.

1998
01:46:17,851 --> 01:46:18,851
'Because, in his diary, Newman said he saw
you that day?

1999
01:46:18,851 --> 01:46:19,851
And thought you could clear his name?'

2000
01:46:19,851 --> 01:46:20,851
'Yes.

2001
01:46:20,851 --> 01:46:21,851
The police said Radcliff told his neighbour
that all he needed was to "find this woman,

2002
01:46:21,851 --> 01:46:22,851
Ruth Keegan.

2003
01:46:22,851 --> 01:46:23,851
She must remember seeing my father that day".'

2004
01:46:23,851 --> 01:46:24,851
'And he told Scanlon,' said Becky, nodding.

2005
01:46:24,851 --> 01:46:25,851
'And Scanlon got scared and followed Radcliff
to Rottnest.'

2006
01:46:25,851 --> 01:46:26,851
The man and the boy sat down at the water's
edge.

2007
01:46:26,851 --> 01:46:27,851
'Scanlon probably couldn't believe his luck
when Radcliff rode out to West End,' said

2008
01:46:27,851 --> 01:46:28,851
Ruth.

2009
01:46:28,851 --> 01:46:29,851
'It was the perfect opportunity to get rid
of him.'

2010
01:46:29,851 --> 01:46:30,851
Becky looked at her.

2011
01:46:30,851 --> 01:46:31,851
'I wonder why he did ride all the way out
there to West End.

2012
01:46:31,851 --> 01:46:32,851
Radcliff, I mean.'

2013
01:46:32,851 --> 01:46:33,851
Ruth spoke slowly.

2014
01:46:33,851 --> 01:46:34,851
'I guess we'll never know.

2015
01:46:34,851 --> 01:46:35,851
Maybe he wanted to see the place where Lizzie
died.

2016
01:46:35,851 --> 01:46:36,851
That was the start of everything that changed
his life so completely - Lizzie's death and

2017
01:46:36,851 --> 01:46:37,851
then his father's.'

2018
01:46:37,851 --> 01:46:38,851
She looked at Becky.

2019
01:46:38,851 --> 01:46:39,851
'But he shouldn't have come to find me.'

2020
01:46:39,851 --> 01:46:40,851
She looked away again.

2021
01:46:40,851 --> 01:46:41,851
And Scanlon didn't need to worry.

2022
01:46:41,851 --> 01:46:42,851
Newman told the police he had seen me on the
beach that day.

2023
01:46:42,851 --> 01:46:43,851
I remember they asked me again and again about
it.

2024
01:46:43,851 --> 01:46:44,851
But I was only seven years old.

2025
01:46:44,851 --> 01:46:45,851
I was building a wonderful sandcastle.

2026
01:46:45,851 --> 01:46:46,851
I didn't see anyone.'

2027
01:46:46,851 --> 01:46:47,851
Becky left Ruth and walked along the beach
back to the cottage.

2028
01:46:47,851 --> 01:46:48,851
Natalie and Amber were still sitting on the
verandah.

2029
01:46:48,851 --> 01:46:49,851
Becky walked through the gate and stood in
the yard.

2030
01:46:49,851 --> 01:46:50,851
'Did you speak to Ruth?' asked Natalie.

2031
01:46:50,851 --> 01:46:51,851
'Yes,' said Becky.

2032
01:46:51,851 --> 01:46:52,851
'Is she okay?'

2033
01:46:52,851 --> 01:46:53,851
'I don't know.'

2034
01:46:53,851 --> 01:46:54,851
Natalie and Amber came to join her.

2035
01:46:54,851 --> 01:46:55,851
Natalie put her arm around Becky's waist.

2036
01:46:55,851 --> 01:46:56,851
'Are you okay?'

2037
01:46:56,851 --> 01:46:57,851
she asked.

2038
01:46:57,851 --> 01:46:58,851
'I think so,' said Becky.

2039
01:46:58,851 --> 01:46:59,851
'Well, it's over now,' said Natalie.

2040
01:46:59,851 --> 01:47:00,851
'And we've still got a few days before we
have to go home.

2041
01:47:00,851 --> 01:47:01,851
So I say, let's forget about Scanlon and Richard
and Lizzie Keegan and anybody who's got Tavis

2042
01:47:01,851 --> 01:47:02,851
in their name,' she smiled, 'and really enjoy
the last few days of our holiday.

2043
01:47:02,851 --> 01:47:03,851
Just the three of us.'

2044
01:47:03,851 --> 01:47:04,851
'Yes,' said Amber, putting her arm around
Becky's shoulder.

2045
01:47:04,851 --> 01:47:05,851
'And we won't talk to any boys.'

2046
01:47:05,851 --> 01:47:06,851
Becky and Natalie looked at each other and
laughed.

2047
01:47:06,851 --> 01:47:07,851
'Come on, let's go for a swim,' said Natalie.

2048
01:47:07,851 --> 01:47:08,851
And they jumped on their bikes and rode through
the middle of the island - between the shallow

2049
01:47:08,851 --> 01:47:09,851
salt lakes and the tea trees, past the barrel
of the old gun and the lighthouse on the hill

2050
01:47:09,851 --> 01:47:10,851
- until they reached Salmon Bay.

2051
01:47:10,851 --> 01:47:11,851
And they spread their towels on the white
sand and ran into the cool, clear green water.

2052
01:47:11,851 --> 01:47:11,853
- THE END -

